01:22:12,510 --> 01:22:15,679
Do like Weir said. Blow the corridor,

979
01:22:16,473 --> 01:22:20,434
separate us from the rest of ship.
Use the foredecks as a lifeboat.

980
01:22:20,936 --> 01:22:23,103
With any luck, TDRS will pick up
our emergency beacon.

981
01:22:23,188 --> 01:22:25,481
We prep the gravity couches,
put ourselves in stasis,

982
01:22:25,565 --> 01:22:27,316
and stand by
for a search and rescue team.

983
01:22:27,400 --> 01:22:29,777
Meantime, I'm gonna go
manually arm these explosives.

984
01:22:29,861 --> 01:22:32,071
- Skipper, will this shit work?
- It worked for Dr Weir.

985
01:22:32,155 --> 01:22:34,448
You go activate the emergency beacon.
You get back here double-quick.

986
01:22:34,532 --> 01:22:36,325
- Yes, sir.
- I'll come with you.

987
01:22:36,409 --> 01:22:38,494
You stay here.
You prep the gravity couches.

988
01:22:38,578 --> 01:22:39,662
Miller.

989
01:22:41,873 --> 01:22:44,208
Close this door behind me, Lieutenant.

990
01:22:54,010 --> 01:22:58,055
<i>WOMAN OVER PA: Gateway opening</i>
<i>in T minus five minutes.</i>

991
01:23:04,437 --> 01:23:06,855
<i>Emergency beacon activated.</i>

992
01:23:08,733 --> 01:23:10,567
Yes.

993
01:23:10,735 --> 01:23:12,069
Blood?

994
01:23:19,411 --> 01:23:21,245
Oh, fuck me.

995
01:23:21,913 --> 01:23:23,414
Fuck me.

996
01:23:24,374 --> 01:23:25,624
Starck!

997
01:23:35,927 --> 01:23:37,594
(STARCK SCREAMING)

998
01:23:48,982 --> 01:23:50,065
Starck!

999
01:23:54,446 --> 01:23:55,821
Run!

1000
01:23:58,491 --> 01:24:02,911
<i>WOMAN OVER PA: Gateway opening</i>
<i>in T minus three minutes.</i>

1001
01:24:06,791 --> 01:24:09,960
<i>Detonator release is authorised.</i>

1002
01:24:10,754 --> 01:24:13,630
<i>The main corridor is now armed.</i>

1003
01:24:13,798 --> 01:24:15,924
We're armed. She's ready to blow.

1004
01:24:16,259 --> 01:24:19,261
I repeat, we are armed.
She's ready to blow.

1005
01:24:19,679 --> 01:24:22,097
Miller. Miller, can you hear me?

1006
01:24:22,182 --> 01:24:24,224
<i>We have to get out of here now.</i>

1007
01:24:24,309 --> 01:24:26,727
(BURNING)

1008
01:24:26,811 --> 01:24:28,520
You let me burn.

1009
01:24:46,164 --> 01:24:50,834
<i>WOMAN OVER PA: Gateway opening</i>
<i>in T minus two minutes.</i>

1010
01:25:07,143 --> 01:25:08,185
Miller.

1011
01:25:26,538 --> 01:25:27,788
(MILLER COUGHING)

1012
01:25:27,872 --> 01:25:29,832
You left me behind.

1013
01:25:32,210 --> 01:25:35,254
No, you're not Edmund Corrick.
I watched him die.

1014
01:25:39,676 --> 01:25:41,135
Weir?

1015
01:25:41,219 --> 01:25:43,137
(CHUCKLING)

1016
01:25:43,721 --> 01:25:47,641
The ship brought me back.
I told you she won't let me leave.

1017
01:25:47,725 --> 01:25:49,935
She won't let anyone leave.

1018
01:25:50,061 --> 01:25:52,855
Did you really think
you could destroy this ship?

1019
01:25:53,189 --> 01:25:56,233
She's defied space and time.

1020
01:25:56,776 --> 01:26:00,279
She's been to a place
you couldn't possibly imagine.

1021
01:26:00,405 --> 01:26:02,114
And now,

1022
01:26:02,574 --> 01:26:06,827
- it is time to go back.
- I know, to hell.

1023
01:26:06,911 --> 01:26:10,289
You know nothing. Hell is only a word.

1024
01:26:10,748 --> 01:26:15,085
The reality is much, much worse.

1025
01:26:17,755 --> 01:26:20,757
Now let me show you.

1026
01:26:22,135 --> 01:26:23,427
Help me!

1027
01:26:26,764 --> 01:26:28,599
No!

1028
01:26:30,643 --> 01:26:32,352
No.

1029
01:26:32,437 --> 01:26:34,188
- You see?
- No.

1030
01:26:34,272 --> 01:26:37,983
They're not dead. They're not dead.

1031
01:26:38,109 --> 01:26:39,484
Not yet.

1032
01:26:39,569 --> 01:26:40,944
(SCREAMING)

1033
01:26:41,279 --> 01:26:43,238
You won't

1034
01:26:43,323 --> 01:26:46,408
take my crew.

1035
01:27:06,179 --> 01:27:10,015
They're not your crew any more.
They belong to the ship.

1036
01:27:10,141 --> 01:27:11,600
<i>WOMAN OVER PA: Gateway opening.</i>

1037
01:27:26,658 --> 01:27:27,991
Take me.

1038
01:27:28,826 --> 01:27:30,702
You take me. You leave them alone.

1039
01:27:30,787 --> 01:27:34,331
No. There is no escape.

1040
01:27:36,459 --> 01:27:38,293
The gateway is open,

1041
01:27:38,378 --> 01:27:41,338
and you are all coming with me.

1042
01:27:46,010 --> 01:27:47,678
Do you see?

1043
01:27:51,975 --> 01:27:53,850
Do you see?

1044
01:27:55,979 --> 01:27:57,354
Do you see?

1045
01:28:00,024 --> 01:28:01,358
Yes,

1046
01:28:02,735 --> 01:28:04,528
I see.

1047
01:28:07,865 --> 01:28:09,574
No!

1048
01:29:30,365 --> 01:29:31,406
Miller.

1049
01:29:38,873 --> 01:29:41,792
<i>MAN ON RADIO: This is Rescue One.</i>
We have contact.

1050
01:29:43,419 --> 01:29:46,797
<i>Approaching the wreckage</i>
of the Event Horizon.

1051
01:29:46,881 --> 01:29:48,465
<i>Prepare to board.</i>

1052
01:29:58,059 --> 01:30:00,435
I'm entering the grav couch bay.

1053
01:30:01,104 --> 01:30:05,107
It doesn't appear to have been damaged
in the explosion.

1054
01:30:06,651 --> 01:30:08,819
There appear to be three survivors:

1055
01:30:09,278 --> 01:30:12,572
Cooper, Justin, Lieutenant Starck.

1056
01:30:13,324 --> 01:30:16,243
Justin seems to have suffered
massive injuries

1057
01:30:16,327 --> 01:30:18,078
but he's still alive.

1058
01:30:19,997 --> 01:30:22,499
The grav couches still have power.

1059
01:30:25,086 --> 01:30:27,337
I'm opening the first tank now.

1060
01:30:37,473 --> 01:30:39,599
It's all right. It's okay.

1061
01:30:39,684 --> 01:30:41,601
- You're safe now.
- Justin, Cooper.

1062
01:30:41,686 --> 01:30:44,020
They're fine. They're with us.

1063
01:30:45,523 --> 01:30:47,190
They're with us.

1064
01:30:49,861 --> 01:30:53,113
- Starck. Starck.
- Stay calm. It's all right.

1065
01:30:53,197 --> 01:30:55,115
- Calm down, it's me.
- Breathe deeply.

1066
01:30:55,199 --> 01:30:56,408
- Starck.
- Breathe deeply.

1067
01:30:56,492 --> 01:30:58,618
- It's the rescue team.
- I need a sedative here, now!

1068
01:30:58,703 --> 01:31:01,621
- I got you, Starck. I got you.
- It's okay.

1069
01:31:01,998 --> 01:31:03,457
I need a sedative here, now!

1070
01:31:03,541 --> 01:31:05,542
Starck, it's the rescue team. We're safe.

1071
01:31:05,626 --> 01:31:08,378
- Okay, okay, I need it now!
- We're safe.

